node.h: sign-extend

* node.h (nd_line): should sign-extend.  shifting `VALUE` extends
  with zero bits if `sizeof(VALUE)` equals to `sizeof(int)`.  the
  zero bits are truncated if `sizeof(VALUE)` is bigger enough.
  [ruby-core:80920] [Bug #13523]
